_source.body:
Federal judge grants temporary restraining order to STOP the Biden administration lifting Title 42 at the border

A judge issued a temporary restraining order to keep Title 42 in place after a lawsuit from Missouri, Louisiana and Arizona 

'This is a huge victory for border security, but the fight continues on,' Missouri attorney general Eric Schmitt wrote on Twitter announcing the news

The Biden administration announced early this month that Title 42 would expire on May 23 

21 states had signed on to the the lawsuit requesting a delay in ending Title 42

According to the New York Post, Hunter Biden’s business partner Eric Schwerin visited the White House a whopping 19 times when Joe Biden was serving as President Barack Obama’s Vice President. Those visits included a November 17, 2010 face-to-face with then-Vice President Biden.

China's Founding Myth

If you want to understand any culture, you must start by studying the myths the culture believes about its founding. In China’s case, this means turning to Han Dynasty historian Sīmǎ Qiān and his seminal work on the subject, The Records of the Grand Historian. One of the first works to attempt a unified history of China from the time of the Yellow Emperor to the 1st Century BC, The Records of the Grand Historian virtually created the China we know today.
